{% if industry == "healthcare" %}
## 7. Industry-Specific Requirements — Healthcare

- All health information is classified as **Restricted** by default
- AI processing of health data must comply with the My Health Records Act 2012
- Ethics committee approval required for AI-assisted clinical decisions
- Patient consent required for AI processing of health information
{% elif industry == "finance" %}
## 7. Industry-Specific Requirements — Finance

- Financial transaction data is classified as **Confidential** minimum
- APRA CPS 234 information security requirements apply
- AI models used for credit decisions must be explainable
- Anti-money laundering (AML) data must remain **Restricted**
{% elif industry == "legal" %}
## 7. Industry-Specific Requirements — Legal

- Client information is classified as **Confidential** minimum due to legal privilege
- AI tools must not compromise client confidentiality or privilege
- Court documents and case materials require special handling
{% elif industry == "government" %}
## 7. Industry-Specific Requirements — Government

- Government data classification follows the Protective Security Policy Framework (PSPF)
- Data labelled OFFICIAL: Sensitive or above is **Restricted** for AI purposes
- Freedom of Information Act considerations apply to AI-generated documents
{% endif %}

