## Appendix B: Definitions and Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| Personal Information | Information or an opinion about an identified individual, or an individual who is reasonably identifiable (Privacy Act 1988 s 6(1)) |
| Sensitive Information | A subset of personal information including health, biometric, genetic data, and information about racial or ethnic origin (Privacy Act 1988 s 6(1)) |
| AI-Inferred Data | New data generated by AI systems through inference, correlation, or derivation from input data |
| Data Minimisation | The principle of collecting and processing only the minimum data necessary for a specific purpose |
| Pseudonymisation | Replacing identifying fields with artificial identifiers while retaining the ability to re-link |
| Anonymisation | Irreversibly removing all identifying information so that the data subject cannot be re-identified |
| Cross-Border Disclosure | Transferring personal information to a recipient outside Australia (APP 8) |
| DPA | Data Processing Agreement — contractual data handling obligations with a vendor |
| APRA | Australian Prudential Regulation Authority |
| PSPF | Protective Security Policy Framework (Australian Government) |

